@startuml
' Include the gradient sprite
sprite redgradrect <svg viewBox="0 0 100 50" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
  <defs>
    <linearGradient id="grad" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="0%">
      <stop offset="0%"  stop-color="#FFCCCC"/>
      <stop offset="50%" stop-color="#FF6666"/>
      <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#990000"/>
    </linearGradient>
  </defs>
  <rect x="5" y="5" width="90" height="40" rx="6" fill="url(#grad)" stroke="#660000" stroke-width="2"/>
</svg>

' Use the sprite in a diagram
Alice -> Bob : Look at this gradient! <$redgradrect>
Bob -> Alice : Nice gradient effect <$redgradrect>

note right of Bob
  The gradient shows:
  <$redgradrect>
  PlantUML now supports
  SVG gradients!
end note
@enduml
